HEADWORD: Tuesday
<hw>Tues"day</hw> <pr>(t⟦umac⟧z"d⟦asl⟧; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>Tewesday</ets>, AS. <ets>Tiwes d⟦ae⟧g</ets> the day of
<ets>Tiw</ets> the god of war; akin to OHG. <ets>Zio</ets>, Icel.
<ets>T⟦ymac⟧r</ets>, L. <ets>Ju</ets>piter, Gr. <grk>Zey`s</grk>;, cf.
OHG. <ets>Ziostac</ets> Tuesday, G. <ets>Dienstag</ets>, Icel.
<ets>T⟦ymac⟧sdagr</ets>. ⟦root⟧244. See <er>Deity</er>, <er>Day</er>,
and cf. <er>Jovial</er>.]</ety> <def>The third day of the week,
following Monday and preceding Wednesday.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

